         <abstract>Dr. Edward Tiryakian taught in the Department of Sociology from 1965 until his retirement in 2004.  He served as Chair of the Department in addition to positions as Visiting Professor abroad.  He was appointed Director for the Center of International Studies in 1988 and served until 1991. The collection contains correspondence and materials related to the Dept. of Sociology, and the Center for International Studies as well as memoranda, clippings and correspondence regarding general University business but also the Nixon Presidential Library controversy and the Allen Building Takeover.  The collection ranges in date from 1963-2008.</abstract>
